Subject: [PATCH] bsp/tanmatsu: transmit Philips-framed I2S to match ES8156 config

The Tanmatsu audio BSP configures the P4's I2S transmitter with
`I2S_STD_MSB_SLOT_DEFAULT_CONFIG` (left-justified / MSB slot format,
`targets/tanmatsu/badge_bsp_audio.c:32`), but `es8156_configure` programs the
ES8156 codec for standard I2S ("Philips") framing (SDP REG11 `sp_protocal=0`,
`es8156.c:1329`). MSB and Philips differ by one BCLK of data delay after each
WS edge, so the codec samples the serial stream one bit skewed from where the
transmitter puts the MSB.

Effect: the codec effectively reads every sample doubled, with the sign bit
wrapping for any sample magnitude ≥ 0.5 FS. This reproduces exactly as onset
crackle on loud transients (attack peaks that cross 0.5 FS wrap; sustained
levels below it don't), is gain-sensitive, present on both the speaker and
headphone outputs, and invisible in the pre-DAC float capture (the tap point
is upstream of the codec, so the wrap only happens on-chip) — see the
analysis in `specs/MEMORY.md` (2026-07-17, "Output-path audit") and
`specs/stages/stage-12-output-path-audit.md` (WO-12a).

Fix: use `I2S_STD_PHILIPS_SLOT_DEFAULT_CONFIG` for the transmitter so its
framing matches the codec's fixed Philips-mode configuration. Only the slot
format changes; bit width, channel mode, clocks, and GPIO wiring are
untouched.

WHY WE CARRY THIS: badge-bsp is a pinned managed component
(`managed_components/badgeteam__badge-bsp`, gitignored, owned by the ESP-IDF
component manager) so this fix cannot be committed there directly. This patch
is applied over the pinned component at build time
(`tools/apply-upstream-patches.sh`) and is intended for upstream submission to
badgeteam/badge-bsp. Retire it once merged and the dependency is bumped. See
`upstream-patches/README.md` and `specs/07-upstream-contributions.md`.

--- a/targets/tanmatsu/badge_bsp_audio.c
+++ b/targets/tanmatsu/badge_bsp_audio.c
@@ -29,7 +29,7 @@

     i2s_std_config_t i2s_config = {
         .clk_cfg  = I2S_STD_CLK_DEFAULT_CONFIG(rate),
-        .slot_cfg = I2S_STD_MSB_SLOT_DEFAULT_CONFIG(I2S_DATA_BIT_WIDTH_16BIT, I2S_SLOT_MODE_STEREO),
+        .slot_cfg = I2S_STD_PHILIPS_SLOT_DEFAULT_CONFIG(I2S_DATA_BIT_WIDTH_16BIT, I2S_SLOT_MODE_STEREO),
         .gpio_cfg =
             {
                 .mclk = BSP_I2S_MCLK,
